  "-103.8 kJ because the DeltaHf of propane is the answer by itself alone": "",
  "DeltaH = [3(-393.5) + 4(-285.8)] - [-103.8 + 5(0)] = [-1180.5 + (-1143.2)] - [-103.8] = -2323.7 + 103.8 = -2219.9 kJ, approximately -2,220 kJ.": "",
  "A student reverses a reaction (DeltaH = -250 kJ) and multiplies it by 3. The new DeltaH is:": "",
